# /run is a fresh tmpfs on every container start, so sshd's required
# privilege-separation directory (/run/sshd, normally created by Debian's
# openssh-server init script, which never runs in this container) has to be
# recreated here every time too - found empirically this session: sshd
# crash-looped with "Missing privilege separation directory: /run/sshd"
# without this line. ssh-keygen -A is idempotent (a no-op for any host key
# type that already exists), so this oneshot is safe to rerun on every
# container start.
if { mkdir -p -m 0755 /run/sshd }
ssh-keygen -A
